  "prompt": "What is the best time of the year to visit Glacier National Park?",
  "response": "The best time to visit Glacier National Park depends on your preferences, but here are some considerations:\n\n1. Summer (July-August)\n- Peak season with warmest temperatures (70-80\u00b0F)\n- All park roads and trails are typically open\n- Most scenic and accessible time\n- Busiest and most crowded period\n- Wildflowers are in bloom\n\n2. Late June and Early September\n- Slightly fewer crowds\n- Pleasant temperatures\n- Most facilities still open\n- Good wildlife viewing opportunities\n\n3. Early Fall (September)\n- Beautiful fall colors\n- Cooler temperatures\n- Less crowded\n- Some facilities start to close\n\n4. Winter (December-March)\n- Best for winter sports like cross-country skiing\n- Very limited access\n- Cold temperatures\n- Most park roads closed\n\n5. Spring (Late May-June)\n- Fewer crowds\n- Wildflowers begin blooming\n- Some snow may remain at higher elevations\n- Not all roads might be open yet\n\nMost experts recommend July and August for the best overall experience, but early September can be an excellent alternative with fewer crowds. Your specific interests (hiking, photography, wildlife) might influence the ideal time for your visit.",
